Program: The History Hour
Title: The Dili Massacre
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04g42p6
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 20 Nov 2016
It is 25 years since Indonesian troops attacked protestors in the East Timorese capital, plus the impact of The Satanic Verses on British society, smuggling endangered birds out of the jungles of South America, a palace burns in Madagascar and the inspiration behind James Bond's theme tune. (Photo: East Timorese activists preparing for the protest that ended in tragedy. Copyright: Max Stahl) Show less